                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <section class="pb-20 px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg prose-gray">
            <p class="lead text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                Last week, I watched my mom download her fourth fitness app this year. "Maybe this one will be different," 
                she said. Three days later, it was deleted. Sound familiar?
            </p>

            <p>
                If you've ever felt overwhelmed, confused, or discouraged by fitness apps, you're not alone. 
                Research shows that 80% of people who download fitness apps stop using them within the first week. 
                But here's the thing: it's not your fault.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">The Problem with Traditional Fitness Apps</h2>

            <p>
                Most fitness apps make three critical mistakes when it comes to beginners:
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">1. They Assume Too Much Knowledge</h3>
            
            <p>
                "Complete 3 sets of Bulgarian split squats, superset with RDLs." If that sentence made you anxious, 
                you understand the problem. Traditional apps throw around terminology like everyone spent years in a gym. 
                They assume you know what proper form looks like, how much weight to use, and when to rest.
            </p>

            <p>
                For beginners, this creates an immediate barrier. You're not just learning to exercise; 
                you're trying to decode a foreign language while your body screams in protest.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. They Start Too Intense</h3>

            <p>
                Most apps begin with a fitness assessment that leaves beginners gasping for air and questioning their life choices. 
                Then they prescribe workouts designed for people who already have a base level of fitness. 
                It's like teaching someone to swim by throwing them in the deep end.
            </p>

            <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6 my-8 text-gray-700 italic">
                "I couldn't walk properly for a week after my first workout. I thought something was wrong with me. 
                Turns out, the app just wasn't designed for true beginners." - Beta tester feedback
            </blockquote>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">3. They Focus on Extremes</h3>

            <p>
                Scroll through any fitness app and you'll see ripped athletes doing impossible-looking exercises. 
                The message is clear: this is what fitness looks like. For beginners carrying extra weight or 
                dealing with limited mobility, these images don't inspire—they intimidate.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">How BurnX Is Different</h2>

            <p>
                At BurnXLabs, we asked ourselves a simple question: What if we built a fitness app specifically 
                for people who've never exercised before? Not simplified workouts for fit people, but a complete 
                reimagining of how beginners start their fitness journey.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">We Speak Your Language</h3>

            <p>
                BurnX uses clear, simple language. We explain everything. When we say "do a squat," we don't assume 
                you know what that means. Our AI coach breaks it down: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. 
                Pretend you're sitting back into a chair. Go as low as feels comfortable."
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">We Start Where You Are</h3>

            <p>
                Your first BurnX workout might be five minutes of gentle movements. That's not a simplified version 
                of a "real" workout—that IS a real workout for where you're starting. We build your fitness 
                foundation slowly, ensuring you feel successful, not defeated.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">We Celebrate Small Wins</h3>

            <p>
                Did you complete a 5-minute workout? That's worth celebrating. Did you choose stairs over the elevator? 
                We notice. BurnX understands that for beginners, consistency matters more than intensity.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-xl p-8 my-12">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">The BurnX Difference:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <span>No fitness jargon - everything explained in plain language</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <span>Workouts that start at your actual fitness level</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <span>AI that adapts to your progress, not the other way around</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                        </svg>
                        <span>Focus on building habits, not breaking records</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">The Future of Beginner Fitness</h2>

            <p>
                We believe the fitness industry has ignored beginners for too long. While other apps compete 
                to offer more advanced features for fitness enthusiasts, we're focused on something more important: 
                helping people take their first steps.
            </p>

            <p>
                Because here's what we know: once you experience success, once you feel that post-workout high, 
                once you notice you're sleeping better and have more energy—you're hooked. The hard part isn't 
                maintaining a fitness routine; it's starting one in a way that doesn't make you want to quit.
            </p>

            <p>
                That's why BurnX exists. Not to create more fitness fanatics (though if that happens, great!), 
                but to help regular people discover that fitness isn't about perfection—it's about progress.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-8 mt-12">
                <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ready to try fitness differently?</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                    Join thousands waiting for a fitness app that actually understands beginners.
                </p>
